Parliament, Thursday 27 August 2020 - Parliament’s Presiding Officers, led by the Speaker of the National Assembly Ms Thandi Modise and National Council of Provinces Mr Amos Masondo, have sent Happy 92nd Birthday wishes to the veteran Inkatha Freedom Party Member of Parliament, Prince Mangosuthu Buthelezi today.
	
	“We wish Prince Buthelezi a blessed birthday. It is an honour and a privilege to have him in our midst as he has consistently exhibited wisdom, remarkable vision and exemplary leadership in the institution. He comes from a selfless and a giving generation worthy of our emulation”, said the Presiding Officers.
	
	“On this day, we wish you good health and thank you for your ethical leadership and guidance. Your fighting spirit and your conquering of Covid19 is inspiring to millions of people in South Africa,’ added the Presiding Officers.
	
	Prince Buthelezi has served as a member of Parliament since 1994 and remains the longest-serving member.
	
	ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENT OF THE REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICAEnquiries: Moloto Mothapo 082 370 6930 Political parties represented in Parliament are entitled to an amount of public money for their political activities. The parties receive the money in proportion to the number of seats they hold. African National Congress on the provincial list for the province of Gauteng